definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-glucose + D-fructose 6-phosphate -eq- UDP + sucrose 6-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-galactose + O-beta-D-xylosylprotein -eq- UDP + 4-beta-D-galactosyl-O-beta-D-xylosylprotein.
Catalysis of the reaction -  NAD(+) + xylitol -eq- D-xylulose + H(+) + NADH.
Catalysis of the transfer of a glucosyl group to an acceptor molecule, typically another carbohydrate or a lipid.
A protein or protein-RNA complex that localizes to one or more of the sex chromosome(s), where it acts to normalize transcription between different sexes.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-phospho-D-glycerate -eq- 3-phospho-D glycerate -  this reaction does not require the cofactor 2,3-bisphosphoglycerate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-phospho-D-glycerate -eq- 3-phospho-D-glycerate -  this reaction requires the cofactor 2,3-bisphosphoglycerate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine(1+) + histamine -eq- N(tau)-methylhistamine + S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + H(+).
A ribonucleoprotein complex formed by the association of the U4|U6 and U5 small nuclear ribonucleoproteins.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine(1+) + trans-aconitate -eq- (E)-2-(methoxycarbonylmethyl)but-2-enedioate + S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (R)-malate + NAD(+) -eq- CO(2) + NADH + pyruvate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (S)-malate + NADP+ -eq- oxaloacetate + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the deacetylation of xylans and xylo-oligosaccharides.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of terminal non-reducing alpha-L-arabinofuranoside residues in alpha-L-arabinosides.
Catalysis of the random hydrolysis of (1--gt-6) linkages in (1--gt-6)-beta-D-glucans.
Catalysis of the endohydrolysis of (1--gt-5)-alpha-arabinofuranosidic linkages in (1--gt-5) arabinans.
Catalysis of the reaction -  an alpha-D-glucuronoside + H2O -eq- an alcohol + D-glucuronate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  beta-D-glucose + O2 -eq- D-glucono-1,5-lactone + H2O2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  O2 + methanol -eq- H2O2 + formaldehyde.
Catalysis of the reaction -  H(+) + oxalate -eq- CO(2) + formate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-dehydroshikimate -eq- 3,4-dihydroxybenzoate + H2O. 3,4-dihydroxybenzoate is also known as protocatechuate.
Catalysis of the 4,5-ring opening reaction -  3,4-dihydroxyphenylalanine + O2 -eq- 4,5-seco-DOPA. 4,5-seco-DOPA spontaneously recyclizes to form betalamic acid.
Catalysis of the reaction -  9-alpha-copalyl diphosphate + H2O -eq- aphidicolan-16-beta-ol + diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-methylbutanol + NAD(P)+ -eq- 3-methylbutanal + NAD(P)H + H+. 3-methylbutanal is also known as isovaleraldehyde.
Catalysis of the reaction -  glyoxal + O2 + H2O -eq- glyoxalate + H2O2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-methyl-5-thio-D-ribulose 1-phosphate -eq- 5-(methylthio)-2,3-dioxopentyl phosphate + H(2)O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-keto-4-methylthiobutyrate + aspartate -eq- methionine + oxaloacetate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  versiconal -eq- versicolorin B + H2O.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of lactone rings (intramolecular cyclic esters) to produce a hydroxyl group and a carboxyl group.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of glucuronosides, yielding free glucuronic acid.
Catalysis of the removal of acetylesters (as acetate) from galacturonic acid residues in the backbone of rhamnogalacturonan.

Catalysis of the cleavage of rhamnogalacturonan, generating oligosaccharides of the form alpha-D-us-galacturonic acid-(1,2)-alpha-L-rhamnose-(1,4)-alpha-D-galacturonate-(1,2)-L-rhamnose-(1,2)-alpha-L-rhamnose-p-(1,4)-alpha-D-galacturonic acid, terminating at the non-reducing end with a hex-4-enopyranosyluronic acid residue.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2 long-chain alcohol + O2 -eq- 2 long-chain aldehyde + 2 H2O.
An extremely narrow tubular channel located between adjacent cells. An instance of this is the secretory canaliculi occurring between adjacent parietal cells in the gastric mucosa of vertebrates.
Increases the rate of GTP hydrolysis by a GTPase of the Rap family.
Catalysis of the transfer of a cation or cations from the inside of the cell to the outside of the cell across a membrane.
Catalysis of the endonucleolytic cleavage to nucleoside 3'-phosphates and 3'-phosphooligonucleotides ending in Gp with 2',3'-cyclic phosphate intermediates.
Catalysis of the oxidative degradation or interconversion of polyamines.
Catalysis of the reaction -  mandelonitrile -eq- cyanide + benzaldehyde.
Catalysis of the isomerization of poly-cis-carotenoids to all-trans-carotenoids.

Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  sulfate(out) + solute(in) -eq- solute(in) + sulfate(out), by a channel in a cell membrane whose opening is governed by the membrane potential.

label.value: lysosomal proton-transporting V-type ATPase, V0 domain

definition.value: The V0 domain of a proton-transporting V-type ATPase found in the lysosomal membrane.
A proton-transporting two-sector ATPase complex found in the lysosomal membrane, where it acts as a proton pump to mediate acidification of the lysosomal lumen.

label.value: lysosomal proton-transporting V-type ATPase, V1 domain

definition.value: The V1 domain of a proton-transporting V-type ATPase found in the lysosomal membrane.
Catalysis of the movement of sphingolipids from one membrane face to the other ('flippase' activity), driven by the hydrolysis of ATP.

Enables the directed movement of sphingolipids into, out of or within a cell, or between cells. Sphingolipids are a class of lipids containing the long-chain amine diol sphingosine or a closely related base (a sphingoid).
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with sphingolipids, a class of lipids containing the long-chain amine diol sphingosine or a closely related base (a sphingoid).

The component of the plasma membrane consisting of the gene products that are tethered to the membrane only by a covalently attached anchor, such as a lipid group, that is embedded in the membrane. Gene products with peptide sequences that are embedded in the membrane are excluded from this grouping.
The action characteristic of a hormone that takes part in the digestion process.

An apical plasma membrane part that forms a narrow enfolded luminal membrane channel, lined with numerous microvilli, that appears to extend into the cytoplasm of the cell. A specialized network of intracellular canaliculi is a characteristic feature of parietal cells of the gastric mucosa in vertebrates.
